
 "Raving Tomatoes - Holy Blasphemy"
 A 4k intro for Breakpoint 2006 by T$ (ts @ deinmeister.de)
 
 Requires DirectX9c (including the D3DX library from the February 2005
 SDK update, stored on disk as d3dx9_24.dll),
 a 3D graphic accelerator featuring VS 2.0, PS 2.0a and a soundcard.
 Initialization can take some time on slower CPUs.

 Running time: 3:34

 Files included:

 The following versions use 32bit color depth and a 24bit z-buffer with 8 stencil bits:
 * Ts4kbp06_512x384.bat
 * Ts4kbp06_640x480.bat
 * Ts4kbp06_800x600.bat
 * Ts4kbp06_1024x768.bat
 * Ts4kbp06_1280x1024.bat

 The is also a cut-down version for anyone who does not have a decent graphic card.
 Please only bother watching it if all other versions failed to work!
 It uses 32bit color depth and a 24bit z-buffer with 8 stencil bits as well:
 * Ts4kbp06_640x480_shaderless_and_ugly.bat

 Color modes used:
 Display format : X8R8G8B8
 Z-/Stencilbuffer format: D24S8
